HEADWORD: Floccose
<hw>Floc*cose"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>floccosus</ets>. Cf. 2d <er>Flock</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Spotted with small tufts like wool.</def>
<rj><au>Wright.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having tufts of soft hairs, which
are often deciduous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Floccular</ent>⟦br⟧
